OL,4,CNazi atrocities in Alderney
OL,6,FDespite the suffering inflicted,
OL,7,Fvirtually none of the German
OL,8,Fperpetrators were ever brought to
OL,9,Fjustice because it emerged that in
OL,10,FSeptember 1945, the British government
OL,11,Fhanded the case over to the USSR who
OL,12,Fdid nothing with it.
OL,14,FLord Pickles explained: "They should
OL,15,Fhave faced British justice. The fact
OL,16,Fthey did not is a stain on the
OL,17,Freputations of successive British
OL,18,Fgovernments."
